# Grading Criteria

The jury will evaluate each project by the following criteria on Demo Day.

| Criteria | Description | Max Points |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Problem Understanding & Solution Fit | Clear articulation of the problem and constraints, Solution matches the requirements and goals, Sensible scope (neither under- nor over-engineered), Clear value of the solution is evident | 10 |
| Architecture & System Design | Clear high-level architecture. Appropriate choice of cloud services and components. Reasonable separation of concerns. Justified build vs. managed decisions. Awareness of scalability, reliability, observability, and failure modes. | 10 |
| Live Demo & System Behavior | System works as presented, Demo supports the claimed functionality, Handling of errors, edge cases, or unexpected behavior, Overall robustness during the live demo | 10 |
| Presentation & Communication | Clear structure and narrative, Understandable explanations (even for non-specialists), Good time management, Confident and precise answers to jury questions | 10 |
| Innovation, Potential & Market Readiness | Originality / novelty of the idea, Clarity of use case and target users, Realistic path to adoption (who would use it, and why?), Feasibility of turning the project into a product or service, Awareness of market, competition, or differentiation | 10 |